LET'S GO RANDOM pinched back early, then settled in the middle of the pack down the backstretch made a mild bid from four wide on the final turn to vie for the lead but tired. FIGHTING SOLDIER was roused to the lead and set most of the pace to the final turn and stopped.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BINDING AGREEMENT was hustled along to be within striking distance down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the turn to take the lead at the top of the stretch while drifting out but was able to hold on for the win. SECRET VISTA raced back down the backstretch then made a four wide bid on the turn, had to move in at the top of the stretch but fought gamely to be second best. HOME VISIT raced in the middle of the pack from the inside then dropped back going into the turn then made a rebid at the quarter pole, moved between horses and was gamely for the show. GOLDEN PALACE raced near the back down the backstretch then moved up on the turn, angled out to six wide in the stretch for a late rally but was not enough. X CLOWN vied for the lead early from the inside then was allowed to settle around the turn, made a rebid in the stretch moving between horses to improve his position. JEB'S LUCKY EIGHT saved ground to no avail. DOCTOR LEO was forwardly placed while going four wide on the turn but lacked the late response. LAURI'S WISH was rushed to the lead from between horses then was collared in mid turn and gave way. SCARLETTSBLACKJACK was away sharply to press the pace to the middle of the turn and weakened. COACH KENNY off step slow and trailed. A JOCKEY OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE JOCKEY OF SECRET VISTA CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF BINDING AGREEMENT FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AT THE TOP OF THE STRETCH, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
